# Atlas reads the SHARED root .env (one level up: ../.env) for keys, then this
# local .env if present. The out-of-the-box setup needs NOTHING here:
# Atlas's default brain (Claude on your Claude Code subscription) needs no key,
# and the delegated jobs use the siblings' own keys (YOUTUBE_API_KEY for Scout;
# Sage's search needs none).

# --- LLM brain (Atlas's own reasoning + persona "ask") -----------------------
# DEFAULT (ATLAS_LLM unset) = Claude on your Claude Code SUBSCRIPTION via the
# Agent SDK. No key required. Do NOT set ANTHROPIC_API_KEY — if set, the SDK
# bills the metered API instead of your subscription (llm.py warns you).
#
# Switch Atlas's brain with ATLAS_LLM (one switch, see llm.py):
#   ATLAS_LLM=gemini     -> needs GEMINI_API_KEY (in the root .env)
#   ATLAS_LLM=deepseek   -> needs DEEPSEEK_API_KEY (in the root .env)
#
# NOTE: ATLAS_LLM controls ATLAS. A delegated JOB runs inside the sibling's
# engine, which reads its OWN switch (SAGE_LLM). `/agents` shows each agent's
# effective provider so the two are never invisible.
# ATLAS_LLM=claude

# Scout needs a YouTube Data API key for its job (kept in the shared root .env):
# YOUTUBE_API_KEY=your-youtube-data-api-v3-key-here
